852
01:00:28,891 --> 01:00:31,519
He hasn't called or been in since Monday.

853
01:00:31,661 --> 01:00:33,390
He left.

854
01:00:33,496 --> 01:00:36,158
He was drinking and we fought, and...

855
01:00:37,567 --> 01:00:39,262
I think he should be back soon.

856
01:00:39,369 --> 01:00:40,427
You okay?

857
01:00:40,737 --> 01:00:41,726
I'm cleaning right now.

858
01:00:41,971 --> 01:00:42,960
He hates it when it's messy.

859
01:00:43,072 --> 01:00:44,164
I'm sorry, but I have to go.

860
01:00:46,342 --> 01:00:49,402
Miss Susan, some people say
it's awfully convenient

861
01:00:49,512 --> 01:00:51,571
for you to forget parts of that night.

862
01:00:51,948 --> 01:00:54,940
But you don't remember parts of the week
following the death, do you?

863
01:00:55,585 --> 01:00:56,609
No, I don't.

864
01:00:57,186 --> 01:00:58,210
How is that?

865
01:00:58,321 --> 01:01:00,619
I mean, how is it that you don't remember
every single detail?

866
01:01:00,723 --> 01:01:01,690
No!

867
01:01:01,791 --> 01:01:05,386
It's cloudy... It's foggy. It's like...

868
01:01:06,729 --> 01:01:08,094
It's like I was in a day dream.

869
01:01:12,168 --> 01:01:14,398
I can see myself
going through certain motions,

870
01:01:14,504 --> 01:01:16,597
but it's just not all there.

871
01:01:40,763 --> 01:01:42,856
-Hello?
-Hi, Susan, it's Joan.

872
01:01:42,999 --> 01:01:45,763
I was just calling to see
if you'd heard from Jeffrey.

873
01:01:46,335 --> 01:01:48,599
-Yes. He came back.
-He did?

874
01:01:49,572 --> 01:01:51,062
-When?
-He's home?

875
01:01:51,174 --> 01:01:53,039
Is he okay? What did he say?

876
01:01:53,576 --> 01:01:56,044
He screamed at me.

877
01:01:56,546 --> 01:02:00,107
And then he took a bleach
and he threw it all over the carpet.

878
01:02:00,283 --> 01:02:03,980
And then he took some shirts and pants
and he left again.

879
01:02:04,087 --> 01:02:07,579
And I have to replace the carpet.

880
01:02:07,824 --> 01:02:10,884
That doesn't really sound like...

881
01:02:12,028 --> 01:02:13,996
Susan, this is Lou. What's going on?

882
01:02:16,766 --> 01:02:17,733
He left.

883
01:02:18,701 --> 01:02:19,895
He left.

884
01:02:24,107 --> 01:02:25,165
Crap!

885
01:02:41,958 --> 01:02:44,051
I need protection. I need...

886
01:02:46,796 --> 01:02:48,354
I don't know what's it called.

887
01:02:48,464 --> 01:02:49,931
-A restraining order?
-Yes.

888
01:02:51,334 --> 01:02:53,268
I keep thinking that I'm hearing him at night.

889
01:02:53,736 --> 01:02:55,499
I just... I know that he's gonna come back.

890
01:02:55,772 --> 01:02:57,034
Okay.

891
01:02:57,340 --> 01:02:59,740
Can you give me your full name?

892
01:03:00,243 --> 01:03:01,835
Susan Lucille Wright.

893
01:03:01,944 --> 01:03:04,071
This is Susan.
We're not here to take your call right now,

894
01:03:04,180 --> 01:03:06,341
so leave a message.

895
01:03:09,018 --> 01:03:10,849
This is Susan.
We're not here to take your call right now...

896
01:03:10,953 --> 01:03:13,581
By Saturday, you'd gone to the doctor,

897
01:03:13,756 --> 01:03:17,556
you'd gone to the cops,
you'd tried bleach, you'd tried paint,

898
01:03:17,660 --> 01:03:21,562
you tried ripping up the carpet,
you'd tried dismantling a king-sized bed,

899
01:03:21,731 --> 01:03:25,326
you'd tried burying the body,
but Rippy sort of messed up,

900
01:03:26,068 --> 01:03:28,332
kind of dug Jeff up, didn't he?

901
01:04:07,510 --> 01:04:08,534
Susan!

902
01:04:09,111 --> 01:04:10,339
Susan, are you all right?

903
01:04:10,446 --> 01:04:13,643
What are you doing out here?
Why don't you come inside, honey?

904
01:04:20,690 --> 01:04:22,988
I think I did something awful, Mom.

905
01:04:23,092 --> 01:04:25,925
Baby, what are you talking about?

906
01:04:29,765 --> 01:04:31,596
I think I killed Jeff.

907
01:04:45,348 --> 01:04:46,679
Hi.

908
01:04:48,451 --> 01:04:51,147
I'm Thomas Dean,
attorney your mother hired.

909
01:04:52,255 --> 01:04:53,984
Thank you for coming.

910
01:04:54,090 --> 01:04:56,718
She said that there was something
you wanted me to see.

911
01:05:10,406 --> 01:05:12,340
Is there anything more?

912
01:05:17,346 --> 01:05:19,337
Oh, my God! Rippy! No!

913
01:05:22,919 --> 01:05:24,750
Oh, my God! Is that a...

914
01:05:27,757 --> 01:05:29,691
He beat me.

915
01:05:29,959 --> 01:05:31,221
He threatened my life.

916
01:05:34,263 --> 01:05:36,288
So this was self defense, right?

917
01:05:38,100 --> 01:05:40,398
What's he gonna do
when he gets home, Mr. Dean?

918
01:05:40,503 --> 01:05:42,471
He's gonna see this awful mess.

919
01:05:42,571 --> 01:05:45,267
-He's gonna be so mad!
-Come on, come on.

920
01:05:47,176 --> 01:05:49,041
You'll be safe here.

921
01:05:49,145 --> 01:05:52,637
But you are not to talk to anyone without me.

922
01:05:52,748 --> 01:05:54,079
Understand? No one.

923
01:05:54,183 --> 01:05:56,743
We'll arrange for a doctor to interview you.

924
01:05:56,852 --> 01:05:58,877
But that's only gonna be
under my supervision,

925
01:05:59,455 --> 01:06:01,047
and that's the only person you can talk to.

926
01:06:01,157 --> 01:06:04,149
Now it is important
that you follow my instructions.

927
01:06:04,360 --> 01:06:05,452
Can you do that?

928
01:06:05,561 --> 01:06:07,119
You a family member?

929
01:06:07,229 --> 01:06:08,218
I'm her lawyer.

930
01:06:09,365 --> 01:06:10,730
Now I'll tell the police what happened.

931
01:06:10,866 --> 01:06:14,131
Eventually, a detective will have
to interview you, but not right now.

932
01:06:14,537 --> 01:06:15,834
We're gonna get through this, okay?

933
01:06:17,406 --> 01:06:19,033
When are the boys coming to visit?

934
01:06:19,342 --> 01:06:20,969
Come on, this way.

935
01:06:27,216 --> 01:06:29,844
There is a body at this address.

936
01:06:29,986 --> 01:06:32,420
I can't say anything more
without breaking attorneylclient privilege,

937
01:06:32,555 --> 01:06:34,284
but you need to send somebody there now.

938
01:06:34,390 --> 01:06:37,757
When you heard
that there was a body found in the house,

939
01:06:37,927 --> 01:06:39,986
whose did you think it was?

940
01:06:40,963 --> 01:06:42,430
I thought it was Susan's.

941
01:06:43,733 --> 01:06:45,496
I thought my best friend was dead.

942
01:06:55,344 --> 01:06:57,869
Do you think the door is locked?

943
01:06:57,980 --> 01:07:00,141
Why are you whispering, Susan?

944
01:07:00,983 --> 01:07:02,382
It started with pushing.

945
01:07:03,452 --> 01:07:06,444
Sometimes he grabs me too hard.
He's on drugs, you know.

946
01:07:07,123 --> 01:07:08,317
Cocaine.

947
01:07:09,125 --> 01:07:13,323
Sometimes he hits me in places
that people can't see.

948
01:07:13,529 --> 01:07:15,224
I'm not supposed to tell anyone.

949
01:07:15,564 --> 01:07:16,861
Why are you whispering?

950
01:07:16,966 --> 01:07:18,399
Because he can hear us.

951
01:07:18,768 --> 01:07:21,066
He's gonna be so mad at me
when he wakes up.

952
01:07:21,404 --> 01:07:23,736
You do realize that Jeffrey is dead,
don't you, Susan?

953
01:07:23,839 --> 01:07:27,070
I mean, you keep referring to him
in present tense.

954
01:07:27,910 --> 01:07:30,572
When he sees the house like that,

955
01:07:30,679 --> 01:07:32,078
he's just gonna kill me.

956
01:07:39,755 --> 01:07:41,518
Let's do it right so we can get it right.

957
01:07:41,957 --> 01:07:44,187
-This is gonna take us three years.
-Yeah.

958
01:07:44,293 --> 01:07:46,557
-What've you got?
-Multiple stab wounds.

959
01:07:46,729 --> 01:07:47,696
How many, give or take?

960
01:07:47,797 --> 01:07:49,128
A hundred, two?

961
01:07:49,231 --> 01:07:50,994
The ME will have to do the math.

962
01:07:51,100 --> 01:07:52,192
Holy crap!

963
01:07:52,334 --> 01:07:53,801
Anybody see the wife?

964
01:07:55,137 --> 01:07:56,161
Anybody talk to the neighbors?

965
01:07:56,272 --> 01:07:59,105
I'll be canvassing the whole area.
Co-workers, everyone.

966
01:08:01,110 --> 01:08:02,702
-Where are the kids?
-Grandmother's.

967
01:08:02,978 --> 01:08:04,809
We just sent someone over there
to talk to her now.

968
01:08:04,947 --> 01:08:06,710
What about the victim's family?
Anybody talk to them?

969
01:08:06,849 --> 01:08:08,214
Get on that.

970
01:08:10,486 --> 01:08:13,216
Hello, everybody. Breaking news today
in the suburb of Cypress Fair

971
01:08:13,322 --> 01:08:16,758
where police are investigating
the murder of a man named Jeffrey Wright

972
01:08:17,059 --> 01:08:19,425
We don't know a lot about Mr. Wright
other than he was a...

973
01:08:19,562 --> 01:08:21,257
-Louis!
-What?

974
01:08:21,964 --> 01:08:25,695
But reports we're getting from the scene
